{"data":{"1":{"id":"1","title":"Polls","slug":"polls","tags":"{\u0022polls\u0022}","current_version":"0.7","supported_versions":"{\u0022Alpha\u0022,\u0022Alpha2\u0022,\u0022Beta\u0022}","views":"0","downloads":"0","featured":"1","status":"1","created":"2012-12-25 13:03:02","modified":"2012-12-25 13:03:02","deleted_time":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","plugin_id":"1","short_description":"Polls is one of the early Official Plugins from AdaptCMS, featuring a fully ready-to-go Polls interface from admin to frontend use.","full_description":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Polls Plugin is a fully featured plugin ready to be integrated with the Modules feature. Polls has an admin area where you can manage polls and it\u0027s related options. Using Modules, Polls has templates setup for frontend use - using AJAX.\u003C\/p\u003E","author_name":"Insane Visions","author_url":"http:\/\/www.insanevisions.com","download_url":"polls.zip","features_text":"\u003Cul\u003E\r\n    \u003Cli\u003E\r\n        \u003Cstrong\u003EEasy Management\u003C\/strong\u003E - Managing Polls is a simple process, enter in a few fields and enter in your options - you\u0027re done!\r\n    \u003C\/li\u003E\r\n    \u003Cli\u003E\r\n        \u003Cstrong\u003EBlock Support\u003C\/support\u003E - To show a poll, you must add a block. You can then pick the specific poll to show and where. Then all you have to do is include the \r\n            poll with the \u0027show_poll\u0027 element and pass the data, the rest is taken care of.\r\n    \u003C\/li\u003E\r\n    \u003Cli\u003E\r\n        \u003Cstrong\u003EStyling Ready to Go\u003C\/strong\u003E - We\u0027ve already styled the poll, setup the javascript and permissions so once you show the poll in your layout or on a specific page,\r\n        you don\u0027t need to do anything else. If you want to change the poll, just update the block. That easy.\r\n    \u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\u003C\/ul\u003E","install_text":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Polls plugin is included and installed by default, but if you delete it manually or picked the no-plugin install, then read below\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\u003Cp\u003ETo install, first download the zip and unpack the folder inside into your \u0027app\/Old_Plugins\u0027 folder - be sure to chmod this new folder to 755. Then login into your admin panel and click on \u0027Manage Plugins\u0027. You should see this plugin listed and an option to install on the right side. Simply click that and click continue on the install and everything should be done!\u003C\/p\u003E","image_url":"http:\/\/adaptcms.charliepage88.com\/uploads\/adaptcms_alpha2_polls_frontend.png"},"2":{"id":"2","title":"Links","slug":"link","tags":"{\u0022links\u0022,\u0022affiliates\u0022}","current_version":"0.8","supported_versions":"{\u0022Alpha\u0022,\u0022Alpha2\u0022,\u0022Beta\u0022}","views":"0","downloads":"0","featured":"0","status":"1","created":"2012-12-25 13:03:02","modified":"2012-12-25 13:03:02","deleted_time":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","plugin_id":"2","short_description":"\u003Cp\u003ELinks is one of the early Official Plugins from AdaptCMS, featuring an admin interface to manage links and using Modules, showing in any way you want your list of links.\u003C\/p\u003E","full_description":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Links Plugin is a fully featured plugin ready to be integrated with the Modules feature. Links has an admin area where you can manage links. Using Modules you ca easily show your links list, including a default template setup.\u003C\/p\u003E","author_name":"Insane Visions","author_url":"http:\/\/www.insanevisions.com","download_url":"links.zip","features_text":"\u003Cul\u003E\r\n    \u003Cli\u003E\r\n        \u003Cstrong\u003EEasy Management\u003C\/strong\u003E - Managing Links is a simple process, a URL and title are the only fields required - but you can also attach an image, set a\r\n        link title, alter the target or set an image from a URL.\r\n    \u003C\/li\u003E\r\n    \u003Cli\u003E\r\n        \u003Cstrong\u003EBlock Support\u003C\/support\u003E - To show a link, you must add a block. You can then set how many links to display and where this should happen. \r\n            Then all you have to do is include the links with the \u0027links list\u0027 element and pass the data, the rest is taken care of.\r\n    \u003C\/li\u003E\r\n    \u003Cli\u003E\r\n        \u003Cstrong\u003EClick Tracking while retaining SEO\u003C\/strong\u003E - With some simple javascript the Links plugin continues to allow for good SEO by keeping the full URL in the a link,\r\n        but the JS will initially stop the click so it can send an AJAX request to update the amount of clicks for this link and then resumes the process.\r\n    \u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\u003C\/ul\u003E","install_text":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Links plugin is included and installed by default, but if you delete it manually or picked the no-plugin install, then read below\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\u003Cp\u003ETo install, first download the zip and unpack the folder inside into your \u0027app\/Old_Plugins\u0027 folder - be sure to chmod this new folder to 755. Then login into your admin panel and click on \u0027Manage Plugins\u0027. You should see this plugin listed and an option to install on the right side. Simply click that and click continue on the install and everything should be done!\u003C\/p\u003E","image_url":null},"3":{"id":"3","title":"Support Tickets","slug":"support-tickets","tags":null,"current_version":"0.5","supported_versions":"{\u0022Alpha\u0022,\u0022Alpha2\u0022,\u0022Beta\u0022}","views":"0","downloads":"0","featured":"0","status":"1","created":"2012-12-27 13:03:02","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","deleted_time":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","plugin_id":"3","short_description":"Support Tickets let you use a simple system for users to submit issues on your site. You can respond back to them and vice-versa, users can attach files to help you troubleshoot problems and you can manage tickets in the admin panel.","full_description":null,"author_name":"","author_url":null,"down